{
  "stem": "15540.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, I, I had no sense of it at all, since I didn't even know I was Jewish, and I didn't know there was a Jewish problem.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I just-- what we were worried about was the Germans and whether the, the Ally would, would win the war.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we followed that.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we, of course, felt the war both because of food rationing and, and having to black, black out windows and having curfews at night.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So those were the kind of things that we, that we felt as far as the war was concerned.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The fighting, there were some bombardment, in '43.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It kind of became more, more obvious.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I remember in 1943 going to dancing school, and on the way home, having to go into a, a, a shelter, because there was a bombardment.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And when we came out from the shelter, there were huge fires, and they had bombarded a sugar factory that was going on fire.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So, so that you could see the-- and, and several times we had to go down in, in our shelter in, in the house, that was built in the house, when there were bombardments.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My father's business was affected.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He, he was under a lot of pressure to produce for the Germans, which he refused to do.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they did have, at some point, German guards in the factory.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He also was approached by the Germans, saying that if he would work for them, they would make sure that he would be saved if there was a action against the Jews.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Mm-hmm.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But needless to say, he, he did not go along with that.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And wouldn't have been saved anyway.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So it was useless.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
